<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,151,429]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,260,285]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1966" box="[669,765,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tlaloc">
<emphasis box="[669,765,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">A. tlaloc</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the body dark-blueish metallic; the head almost triangular; the mandible narrow and with its teeth equally wide; the clypeus with the clypeal carina higher than frons level; the eye large; and the vertex concave, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1966" box="[837,935,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tlaloc">
<emphasis box="[837,935,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">A. tlaloc</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the body dark green metallic; the head wide; the mandible wide, curved, and step-shaped with five distal teeth; the clypeus with the clypeal carina lower than frons level; the eye small; and the vertex straight.
</paragraph>
